2. What does this enable? → Access to cloud metadata endpoint
3. Test metadata → http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/
4. Exploitation → Extracted AWS credentials, escalated to full account compromise

CHAIN CATEGORIES TO CONSIDER:
- SSRF → Cloud Metadata → Credential Theft
- SQLi → File Write (INTO OUTFILE) → RCE
- LFI → Log Poisoning → RCE
- XXE → SSRF → Internal Service Access
- IDOR → Admin Account Access → Privilege Escalation
- XSS → Session Hijacking → Account Takeover
- Auth Bypass → Admin Panel → User Management → Full Compromise
- Info Disclosure → Version Detection → CVE Exploit → RCE

The correlation_engine will automatically suggest chains when you confirm findings.
ALWAYS review and pursue these suggestions - they lead to critical vulnerabilities.
