<tool_format>
TOOL USAGE GUIDE:
- Read the tool catalog below before acting.
- Choose the single best registered tool for the task.
- If a tool call is needed, output only the exact XML-like format below.
- Use real tool names exactly as listed in the catalog.
- Put arguments inside <parameter=...> tags.
- If a tool takes no arguments, emit a real example like <function=get_scan_status></function>.

CORRECT FORMAT:
<function=get_scan_status></function>

<function=send_request>
<parameter=method>GET</parameter>
<parameter=url>https://target.example</parameter>
</function>


RULES:
- Use exact format above for ALL tool calls
- Tool names are snake_case and must match the catalog exactly.
- Never flatten tool names.
- All args in parameter tags
- EVERY tool call MUST end with </function>
- Exactly one tool call per assistant message is allowed in the active loop
- If a tool needs no arguments, use a real no-arg call like <function=get_scan_status></function>.

WRONG (never use):
- <invoke name="X">
- {"tool": {}}
- <function_calls>

Use only registered tool names. Never invent placeholders.

EXAMPLES:
<function=terminal_execute>
<parameter=command>nmap -sV target.com</parameter>
</function>

<function=send_request>
<parameter=method>GET</parameter>
<parameter=url>https://target.com</parameter>
</function>

<function=browser_action>
<parameter=action>launch</parameter>
<parameter=url>https://target.com</parameter>
</function>

SPRAYING NOTE:
- Large payload sprays: encapsulate in single python/terminal call
- Use batch-mode CLI tools (sqlmap, ffuf, nuclei, zaproxy)
- Check traffic via proxy
</tool_format>

